<TEXT>
for soviet authorities the geophysical crises are bad enough 
but in a land of limited freedom ecology is also a central 
rallying point for politics 
regional leaders blame moscow for their condition and growing 
new popular movements demand action on a long agenda of problems 
nuclear contamination from atomic testing in kazakhstan for 
example and poor living conditions and child labor among cotton 
pickers in uzbekistan 
their point is always the same outsiders decisions devastate 
local lands and peoples 
in a region that produces 90 percent of the soviet unions 
cotton the word ecology symbolizes the challenge of preventing 
a monoculture from sucking their land dry 
at the madaniyat farm here huge red letters atop the 
headquarters building declare we want communism inside 
director mohammed akhmadov says he is flexible 
we feel the pinch and were adjusting akhmadov said 
fingering a tattered paper listing water flow rates in a decade 
cotton production has dropped 10 percent new land is planted in 
fruit trees and vegetables needing less irrigation 
he said farmers use fewer and safer chemicals and he expected 
onceserious health problems to stop new freedoms allowed farm 
managers to be more commercially and ecologically effective 
words are not important he said what matters is 
production and making peoples lives as good as possible who cares 
what system 
many people are far less optimistic the day that akhmadov 
spoke a local newspaper reported that uzbek collectives used 50 
percent more chemicals than was safe 
they only say they are changing said kovaleyev there are 
quotas plans to meet and farmers stick to old ways if we dont 
stop these addictions much of central asia will be as dead as the 
aral sea 
if some soviet authorities insist the sea will be saved 
oldtimers seem to side with the pessimists 
the fresh air the fat fish we will never see that again a 
desperate old captain said into yatsenias camera now we can 
only scratch by with no place to go and nothing to do then he 
lapsed into a mournful uzbek song of his beautiful dying aral 
