<TEXT>
rain fell along lake erie and dampened the northwest early 
today the rest of the nation had mostly dry weather 
fog clung to mountainsides in kentucky tennessee and virginia 
and along stretches of the new england seaboard new orleans also 
had fog 
the midwest and plains had mostly dry weather and the west was 
mostly cloudfree 
it was raining early today at cleveland and as far south as 
pittsburgh a thunderstorm tapered off to a drizzle in buffalo ny 
rain also fell along the western edge of the rockies in 
washington and oregon 
todays forecast called for hot and humid weather along the east 
and gulf coasts in front of a cold front extending down the 
appalachians and inland across the south to texas 
scattered thunderstorms and showers along the front were 
expected to develop from maine to louisiana but little rain was 
expected in many areas 
showers were likely over central and west texas and rains were 
again likely to cause flooding in the region 
the forecast also called for dry weather across the midwest the 
central and upper plains and the midmississippi and ohio valleys 
temperatures were expected to soar into the 100s in the desert 
southwest and hit the 90s as far north as montana 
some relief was expected today in the northwest as a cold front 
was likely to usher in lower temperatures 
