forecasters said the minimal hurricane could reach the canadian 
provinces by wednesday but some effects would be felt today 
because hurricaneforce winds extended 70 miles from the center and 
tropical stormforce winds of at least 39 mph reached outward up to 
350 miles 
at 6 am edt today bertha was centered near latitude 383 
north longitude 660 west said forecasters at the national 
hurricane center in suburban coral gables the hurricane was thus 
centered some 775 miles due east of washington dc or 450 miles 
southsouthwest of halifax nova scotia 
it was moving northnortheast at 13 mph and had top sustained 
winds of 75 mph 
bertha the first hurricane of the 1990 atlantic season was 
expected to stay at the same strength course and speed through 
early wednesday said forecaster hal gerrish 
bertha had been downgraded sunday night to a tropical storm 
after it temporarily weakened regained enough strength to push it 
just over the hurricane threshold of 74 mph 
earlier bertha kicked up the surf along carolina beaches and 
sent gusts up to about 45 mph toward bermuda but it has spent much 
