<TEXT>
the soviet defense ministry said today that a 
ukrainian resolution to keep its army conscripts from serving 
outside the republic could impair the soviet unions ability to 
defend itself 
the republics parliament on monday adopted a resolution 
declaring that ukrainians drafted into the soviet army should not 
be used to quell ethnic violence in other parts of the country 
such as armenia and kirghizia 
lawmakers of the countrys second most populous republic 
addressed the resolution to the supreme soviet of the ussr and 
expressed the view that ukrainian conscripts should only serve in 
the republic the interfax news agency said 
the resolution also said that ukraininan troops attached to the 
republics interior ministry should not be used to put down ethnic 
clashes in other republics 
they appealed to the supreme soviets of azerbaijan armenia 
kirghizia and uzbekistan to provide law and order on their 
territories themselves interfax reported from kiev 
asked to comment on the resolution defense ministry spokesman 
vladimir nikanorov said our approach to forming armed forces of 
the ussr is that they must be a socialist multinational 
exterritorial and professional army 
from a military point of view it is a step backward it can 
lead to the ruining of the armys capabilities and impair the 
countrys defense he said 
furthermore economically and technically it is not really 
feasible politically it can lead to transferring interethnic 
differences into military conflicts he said 
the ukrainian parliament on july 16 declared that its laws take 
precedence over national law the declaration said the republic had 
the right to set up its own armed force currency citizenship and 
banking system 
the declaration said the republics youth cannot perform 
military service outside the republic without the parliaments 
permission 
the ukrainian decree followed other republics such as russia 
and the three baltic states clamoring for more independence from 
