their highest level in four months the government reported today 
the commerce department said new home sales totaled a seasonally 
adjusted annual rate of 581000 units in june after gaining a 
revised 23 percent in may the june figure was the highest level 
since february when sales totaled 606000 at an annual rate 
the may increase was even stronger than the 04 percent advance 
first reported last month before the may increase new home sales 
had dropped for five straight months 
at the same time inventories of new homes fell to a 75month 
backlog at the june sales pace that was down from 82 months in 
may and 84 months in april 
the increased sales and lower inventories could stimulate 
renewed construction in an industry that analysts have said was 
slowed by high interest rates consumer caution because of adverse 
economic news and a glutted market 
