of the typical family to purchase a medianpriced existing home was 
1029 in june down from 1047 in may 
that means a family earning the national median income of 
34250 in june had 1029 percent of the income needed to qualify 
for conventional financing covering 80 percent of a medianpriced 
home costing 97500 
the median income means that half of the families earned more 
and half less while the median price means half of the homes cost 
more and half less 
in its report the commerce department said the median price of 
a new home rose 16 percent to 129900 while the average price 
advanced 21 percent to 152900 
