community to dismantle barriers among them are expected to create 
five to six million new jobs in service research and development 
this is happening just as scientists from eastern europe are 
getting a new chance to move schambra pointed out 
meanwhile he said australia new zealand and canada have 
policies to attract highly skilled immigrants 
how we deal with this issue will to a large degree determine 
the pace of research progress on aids cancer treatment and other 
public health priorities he predicted 
the laws the scientists want to change favor the admittance of 
foreigners related to people already in the united states 
