to try a livelier role in spartacus which requires a lot of 
marching and lunging and dashing here and there 
im not a dancer at all he said grinning i dont take 
part in any strenuous athletics for exercise the only thing i do 
is rifle shooting i also mow the lawn and saw some firewood 
as woodruff walked out the door peasley was barking left 
right left right to the 19 finalists as they marched across the 
floor to piano music from aram khachaturians score 
grabbing a wooden spear peasley said these are held like you 
hold a thermometer grasp them in the center and keep them under 
your armpit like this 
he taught the neophyte gladiators how to sway without getting 
dizzy and how to crouch without looking like youre sitting on 
the toilet 
he held a roman warriors shield to his chest you must be 
careful how you hold a shield or they begin to look like a 
handbag he said 
the extras or supernumeraries will receive 28 for four 
rehearsals and 40 for four performances of spartacus starting 
friday the pay is somewhat higher than the usual rate for opera 
supers because of the ballets complex stage movements 
the money wasnt the lure for woodruff 
i have no illusions about being a great actor he said i 
do it for the fun of it its a chance to do theater thats 
bigtime without having any real professional skills 
