could the leader said its more of a standoff 
leaders urging neutrality contend that the abortion issue is 
just too divisive for the labor movement and a prochoice stand 
would threaten unions organizing efforts 
those officials complained that abortion had nothing to do with 
traditional collective bargaining issues such as hours and pay 
but prochoice forces noted that the aflcio has gotten involved in 
other social issues such as civil rights 
