plunged this caribbean nation of 13 million residents off 
northeast venezuela into chaos 
on monday night robinson had said by telephone that he had 
accepted an agreement under which he would resign and bakr and his 
men would be granted amnesty 
but government officials said today that no such agreement 
existed and that robinson had made the statement under duress 
bakr said earlier today that the rebels agreed that winston 
dookeran the deputy prime minister would replace robinson when he 
steps down dookeran was released from the parliament building 
friday 
the interim government would be a coalition consisting of 
representatives of all major political parties along with bakrs 
jamaat almuslimeen group 
the group which is believed to number 250 to 300 has blamed 
robinson for widespread poverty in this onceoil rich caribbean 
nation near venezuela it has little support among the populace 
bakr is a former policeman who converted to islam in 1980 and 
has long considered himself a champion of the downtrodden he 
founde jamaat almuslimeen which means the moslem group in arabic 
in 1984 
robinson easily won parliamentary elections in 1986 under the 
constitution the next elections dont have to be held until 1991 
on monday security forces exchanged gunfire with the rebels at 
parliament and at the government television station three 
buildings in and around the tv complex were set ablaze but no 
injuries were reported 
at least nine people six rebels two police officers and a 
civilian have been killed since the siege began and the 
instability has spawned massive looting in trinidad and tobago a 
twoisland nation of 13 million people state radio said some 
looters were shot monday but gave no details 
bakr has ties to libya and it is believed he has received 
funding from that country in a conversation with local radio 
today he said he had no regrets over what he had done 
i hope we can settle it in love he said 
asked if the siege could end in violence he said everyone 
will die at some time in their lives 
