leaders of the palestinian uprising said 
tuesday they were forming a higher judicial committee to try to 
reduce the killings by palestinians of arabs suspected of 
collaborating with israel 
the announcement came in a leaflet distributed in the occupied 
territories and signaled the first national institution to be 
founded for the wouldbe state of palestine 
the insurgency against israeli occupation in the west bank and 
gaza strip began in december 1987 and is backed by the palestine 
liberation organization 
leaders of the uprising acted amid a rise in the murders of 
palestinians suspected of collaborating with israeli authorities 
in july palestinians killed 15 fellow arabs for informing or 
collaborating in other ways according to figures compiled by the 
associated press 
in contrast three palestinians died in july as a result of 
clashes with israeli troops and a fourth arab was killed in a 
prison breakout according to the israeli information center for 
human rights in the occupied territories 
