israeli soldiers and civilians and 45 israelis have been killed by 
palestinians a further 243 palestinians were slain by fellow 
arabs most on suspicion of collaborating 
the judicial committee appeared to be a first step by local 
palestinians toward creating a bureaucracy to deal with internal 
problems 
most palestinians reject dealings with israeli police and 
military courts especially after the plo declared an independent 
state in the occupied lands in 1988 
israel rejects formation of a palestinian state many third 
world countries recognize the wouldbe state but not major western 
governments 
