commission representative blanton moore and mckinney met with coast 
guard capt thomas greene in galveston to discuss the proposal 
greene said the coast guard was hesitant to grant permission 
we want to be careful there isnt something else introduced into 
the area that could cause more problems he said 
in austin land commissioner garry mauro criticized the response 
to the spill 
the point is this oil spill occurred saturday at 230 pm 
all these decisions should have been made in advance of this 
spill mauro told a news conference 
were not happy with that either said coast guard chief 
petty officer todd nelson 
the greek tanker shinoussa collided with two of three barges 
being towed by the tugboat chandy n south of redfish island 15 
miles north of galveston 
one barge nearly sank and the other listed both spewed 
catfeed oil a refinery oil similar to no 5 oil into the bay 
