and i still find them strange this morning vincent said 
a baseball official speaking on the condition of anonymity 
said vincent had proposed suspending steinbrenner for two years and 
putting him on three years probation 
steinbrenner agreed to give up control of the team and resign as 
general partner by aug 20 
on tuesday the commissioner placed the yankees under american 
league supervision for the next five years he also barred all 
contact between steinbrenner and the team without vincents 
permission that would apply to steinbrenners son if he became 
manager 
steinbrenner confirmed tuesday that he wants his 33yearold 
son hank to take over the daytoday operations of the yankees 
the move already cleared by vincent must still be approved by the 
teams limited partners and major league clubs 
i have no desire to return as general partner steinbrenner 
said that will rest with my sons i have other endeavors which i 
plan to devote most of my available time to now which are very 
important to me 
vincent ordered that for five years the yankees must seek league 
approval for the hiring firing promotion demotion or 
reassignment of any officer of the club during that time the 
team also must ask league approval to sue or file a grievance 
against a player and to hire lawyers and investigators involved 
with player dealings 
steinbrenner would be allowed to consult with team managers in 
four areas television and radio contracts concessions agreements 
governmental and lease agreements and banking relationships 
vincent also barred phil mcniff the american shipbuilding co 
executive who headed steinbrenners investigation of winfield from 
having anything to do with the yankees winfield eventually was 
traded to california 
mcniff supervised steinbrenners relationship with spira who is 
