here at a glance is a comparison of 
president bushs proposed spending for various military weapons and 
the changes approved by the house and senate armed services 
committees for the fiscal year beginning oct 1 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
bush proposed spending 307 billion on defense the senate armed 
services committee approved a 289 billion the house panel adopted 
a 283 billion bill actual spending must be done through separate 
appropriations bills 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
in january bush called for a total of 55 billion for five 
planes next year and advanced procurement money for 10 planes the 
following year defense secretary dick cheney announced a revision 
in april that proposed two planes in 1991 and advanced procurement 
of six planes in 1992 at a cost of 46 billion the senate 
committee agreed with the revised plan the house panel eliminated 
all procurement money and included only enough funds to cancel the 
program after the 15 planes currently under development 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
bush proposed 47 billion for the program commonly known as 
star wars the senate panel cut nearly 1 billion for a total of 
37 billion the house committee slashed close to 2 billion for a 
total of 29 billion 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the presidents request included 16 billion for procurement 
and military construction costs and 548 million for research 
involved with moving the mx nuclear missile from fixed silos to 
railroad cars the senate committee approved only the research 
money the house panel eliminated all money for the program and 
instead created a fund of 600 million for advanced missile work 
calling on bush to decide in 90 days what it should be used for 
the mx or the unbuilt midgetman 
</TEXT>
