the idea 
and former gov carlos romero barcelo of the prostatehood new 
progressive party said any effort to determine who would be 
eligible to vote would be a logistical nightmare 
pena clos noted that puerto rico has about 35 million people 
about 21 million of whom eligible to vote 
how can 25 million people living in the united states be 
allowed to affect the future of those on the island he asked 
miguel colom who moved to new york 12 years ago agrees that he 
and others living here have no business voting on the islands 
future 
im an american thats it he said 
why should they vote if they live here theyre not affected 
