<TEXT>
newmarketonfergus ireland ap the worlds leading 
agriculture ministers tuesday expressed reservations about a 
surprise european proposal to cut farm aid worldwide but said it 
was a step forward 
the european communitys agriculture commissioner ray macsharry 
of ireland on monday proposed cutting world farm aid by 30 percent 
over a decade intensifying the debate over europes huge farm 
subsidies 
the dispute over europes support for its farmers will not as 
feared block the successful conclusion in december of current 
global trade liberalization talks the senior officials said 
macsharry and the agriculture ministers of the united states 
japan canada and australia made their comments at a news 
conference at the conclusion of a twoday private meeting 
us agriculture secretary clayton yeutter said the proposal is 
only a start in the negotiating process 
much of the rest of the world is in my judgment prepared to go 
much further down the road of agricultural trade reform than what 
is implied by mr macsharrys proposal he said we have a lot 
of negotiating ahead to bridge those gaps 
canadas agriculture minister donald mazankowski said its 
certainly a welcome step but he added it is very difficult to 
determine in fact whether export subsidies will be cut under the 
proposal at all 
trade negotiations are being held in geneva under the general 
agreement on tariffs and trade 
the united states and 14 other farm exporting countries want the 
12nation ec to end its export credits system and cut direct 
subsidies for farmers which the critics say distort trade 
macsharry said his proposal was serious and balanced but 
conceded that we have a number of important differences these 
remain to be resolved 
mazankowski told reporters earlier that the united states and 
canada already may have implemented cuts such as those proposed 
macsharrys proposed 30 percent cut in farm support extends from 
1986 to 1996 it includes already implemented ec reductions of 10 
percent in support for crops and 15 percent for livestock 
a final proposal is to be presented in september to the european 
community which must approve the plan before it could be tabled at 
gatt 
gatt negotiators are to meet again in geneva in late august 
they agreed at a meeting last week to compile lists and costs of 
their farm support by oct 1 
the agriculture ministers meeting was held at dromoland castle 
near shannon in western ireland 
