procter amp gamble co said tuesday it had 
sued a southeast kansas couple for allegedly spreading rumors 
which it has denied for years that the company was associated 
with satanism 
the suit filed late monday in us district court alleges that 
james and linda newton of parsons have made libelous and malicious 
statements about procter amp gamble by saying it supports the 
church of satan 
the couple also allegedly urged people to boycott procter amp 
gamble products 
a company news release said the newtons are distributors of 
household items for rival amway home products as were several 
individuals who previously admitted spreading these lies 
it appears they are trying to enhance their own business 
said topeka attorney edwin smith representing procter amp gamble 
the company is seeking more than 50000 in damages and is 
asking the court to order the newtons to stop circulating the 
stories 
mrs newton reached at her home declined to comment 
the suit is one of a number the cincinnatibased company has 
filed over the years in an attempt to fight persistent rumors that 
its moon and stars trademark is a satanic symbol 
the 108yearold trademark features a maninthemoon figure a 
popular design of the 1800s overlooking a field of 13 stars the 
company says are to honor the original american colonies 
were very proud of our company trademark symbolizing procter 
amp gamble quality and excellence edwin l artzt chairman and 
chief executive officer said in a news release 
these lies have persisted now for 10 years and we will file 
further suits if necessary he said 
