<TEXT>
the federal communications commission on 
tuesday approved the 125 billion merger of longdistance 
telephone companies mci communications corp and telecom usa inc 
the merger is expected to help mci make greater inroads into the 
longdistance telephone market dominated by american telephone amp 
telegraph co 
mci spokeswoman kathleen keegan said the company expects the 
merger to be completed before the end of august pending state 
regulatory approvals 
mci announced last april it would acquire all outstanding shares 
of telecom common stock for 42 a share for a total purchase price 
of about 125 billion 
mci which has headquarters in washington is the nations 
second largest provider of longdistance service it has 19500 
employees and had revenue in 1989 of 65 billion mci serves 
residential and commercial customers with long distance voice and 
data services in the united states and overseas 
telecom usa is the fourth largest us long distance company 
based in atlanta it has 5000 employees and had 1989 revenue of 
713 million 
